NATO chief to make Bosnia visit 
NATO Secretary General Javier Solana will meet with members of the
Bosnian presidency during a visit to Sarajevo Friday and have talks
with the commander of the NATO-led peacekeeping force SFOR, US General
William Crouch.
Solana will also meet Bosnia's deputy civilian peace coordinator
Michael Steiner and representatives of civilian organizations, a
statement issued by the North Atlantic Treaty Organization said.
Solana will be accompanied by the supreme commander of NATO forces in
Europe, General George Joulwan.
